	Shooter Grant    
	 London, Dec. 26 (PTI): When he was a child, actor Hugh Grant had a gala time learning how to shoot at his grandparents farm in Scotland during Christmas holidays.      
	The Notting Hill star admits he was around six or seven when his grandfather first handed him a gun and taught him how to fire the weapon, reports www.Contactmusic.com.      
	My grandfather was a military man and he thought it was important to teach kids how to kill, Grant said. The actor said his grandfather made life-sized human cutouts for the children to shoot at.    
	Cate home    
	 London (PTI): Actress Cate Blanchetts old home, along with a designer bathtub, is up for sale. Blanchett had shifted into the Grade I listed townhouse in Brighton a few years ago and had to close off a whole street in order to have the enormous stone bath winched into the house.The star, who lives in Sydney, later sold the house to songwriter Richard Stannard.    
	Present pair    
	 London (PTI): Singing sisters Kylie and Danii Minogue get into a competitive spirit during Christmas, battling it out to buy the best presents for the festive season.The Australian stars traditionally spend the holiday season back in their native country with their family and Dannis always vying with her sister over what goes under the tree, reports Heat magazine.    
	Lohan trip    
	 New York (PTI): Lindsay Lohan has returned from her humanitarian trip to India a changed woman, her mother Dina Lohan has claimed. She also says that Lindsay was humbled and moved by the plight of the children she saw while filming a BBC documentary about human trafficking in India, reports the New York Post.    
	Butler king    
	 London (PTI): He made a major breakthrough in Hollywood with his portrayal of King Leonidas in 300, a role actor Gerard Butler feels was destined to be his. The Scottish actor had played a king in an early Christmas pageant in school, which he thinks, prepared him for his role in the epic movie, reports Empire magazine.     
	Fun Jessica    
	 Los Angeles (PTI): Actress Jessica Simpson is set to launch her new swimwear range which the star says is fun and flirty, but still so classic. The 29-year-old actress has collaborated with bathing suit purveyor Red Carter for the line which will be launched this month, reports People.                                                                                                                                                            
